<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy - <%= typeof botName !== 'undefined' ? botName : 'Valknut' %></title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.0/css/all.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('partials/navbar') %>

    <main class="container my-5">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-10 mx-auto">
                <div class="card bg-dark text-white border-secondary">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h1 class="h2 mb-0">
                            <i class="fas fa-shield-alt me-2"></i>
                            Privacy Policy
                        </h1>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="text-muted mb-4">
                            <i class="fas fa-calendar-alt me-2"></i>
                            Last updated: January 17, 2026
                        </p>

                        <section class="mb-5">
                            <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="fas fa-info-circle me-2"></i>1. Introduction</h2>
                            <p>
                                Welcome to <%= typeof botName !== 'undefined' ? botName : 'Valknut' %>. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your
                                personal data. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your data
                                when you use our Discord bot and web dashboard.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                By using our services, you consent to the terms of this privacy policy and the processing
                                of your data as described here.
                            </p>
                        </section>

                        <section class="mb-5">
                            <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="fas fa-database me-2"></i>2. What data do we collect?</h2>

                            <h3 class="h5 mb-3">2.1 Discord User Data</h3>
                            <p>When you use our bot or log into our dashboard, we collect the following data from Discord:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Discord user ID</strong> - For identification and authentication</li>
                                <li><strong>Username</strong> - For display in the dashboard</li>
                                <li><strong>Avatar</strong> - For visual representation</li>
                                <li><strong>Email address</strong> - If shared via Discord OAuth</li>
                                <li><strong>Server (guild) memberships</strong> - To determine which servers you can manage</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h3 class="h5 mb-3 mt-4">2.2 Server Configuration Data</h3>
                            <p>For servers where our bot is installed, we store the following data:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Server ID and name</strong> - For identification</li>
                                <li><strong>Configuration settings</strong> - Such as log channels, moderation settings</li>
                                <li><strong>Roles and permissions</strong> - For access management</li>
                                <li><strong>Backup data</strong> - If you use the backup feature</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h3 class="h5 mb-3 mt-4">2.3 Authentication and Security</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Session cookies</strong> - To track your login session</li>
                                <li><strong>2FA (Two-Factor Authentication) data</strong> - If enabled by you</li>
                                <li><strong>Remember device tokens</strong> - For remembering trusted devices (2FA)</li>
                                <li><strong>Login timestamps</strong> - For security purposes</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h3 class="h5 mb-3 mt-4">2.4 Technical Data</h3>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>IP addresses</strong> - In server logs for security and debugging</li>
                                <li><strong>Browser information</strong> - For technical support</li>
                                <li><strong>Activity logs</strong> - To track moderation actions</li>
                            </ul>
                        </section>

                        <section class="mb-5">
                            <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="fas fa-cogs me-2"></i>3. How do we use your data?</h2>
                            <p>We use your data for the following purposes:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Authentication</strong> - To identify you and grant access to the dashboard</li>
                                <li><strong>Functionality</strong> - To provide bot and dashboard features</li>
                                <li><strong>Configuration</strong> - To store and apply your server settings</li>
                                <li><strong>Security</strong> - To prevent unauthorized access</li>
                                <li><strong>Moderation</strong> - To track and execute moderation actions</li>
                                <li><strong>Support</strong> - To resolve technical issues</li>
                                <li><strong>Improvement</strong> - To improve our services (anonymized where possible)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </section>

                        <section class="mb-5">
                            <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="fas fa-cookie-bite me-2"></i>4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
                            <p>We use the following types of cookies:</p>

                            <div class="table-responsive">
                                <table class="table table-dark table-striped">
                                    <thead>
                                        <tr>
                                            <th>Cookie Type</th>
                                            <th>Purpose</th>
                                            <th>Duration</th>
                                        </tr>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Session cookies</strong></td>
                                            <td>Login session management</td>
                                            <td>Until logout</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Remember me cookie</strong></td>
                                            <td>Remember 2FA device</td>
                                            <td>30 days</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td><strong>Cookie consent</strong></td>
                                            <td>Remember your cookie preference</td>
                                            <td>1 year</td>
                                        </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                </table>
                            </div>

                            <p class="mt-3">
                                <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle text-warning me-2"></i>
                                <strong>Important:</strong> Without accepting cookies, you cannot log into the dashboard.
                            </p>
                        </section>

                        <section class="mb-5">
                            <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="fas fa-share-alt me-2"></i>5. Do we share your data?</h2>
                            <p>We <strong>never</strong> sell or rent your personal data to third parties. We only share your data in the following situations:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Discord</strong> - For authentication via Discord OAuth2</li>
                                <li><strong>Legal obligation</strong> - If required by law</li>
                                <li><strong>Security</strong> - To prevent fraud or abuse</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>We do not share data with advertisers or marketing companies.</p>
                        </section>

                        <section class="mb-5">
                            <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="fas fa-lock me-2"></i>6. How do we protect your data?</h2>
                            <p>We take the security of your data seriously and implement various security measures:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Encryption</strong> - All communication uses HTTPS/TLS</li>
                                <li><strong>Password hashing</strong> - 2FA secrets are securely stored</li>
                                <li><strong>Access control</strong> - Only authorized users have access</li>
                                <li><strong>Database security</strong> - Our database is secured with authentication</li>
                                <li><strong>Regular updates</strong> - We keep our systems up-to-date</li>
                                <li><strong>Backups</strong> - Regular backups to prevent data loss</li>
                            </ul>
                        </section>

                        <section class="mb-5">
                            <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="fas fa-clock me-2"></i>7. How long do we retain your data?</h2>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>User data</strong> - Until you delete your account or leave the bot</li>
                                <li><strong>Server configuration</strong> - Until the bot is removed from the server</li>
                                <li><strong>Session data</strong> - Until the end of your session or after inactivity</li>
                                <li><strong>Logs</strong> - Maximum 90 days for debugging and security</li>
                                <li><strong>Backups</strong> - According to your backup retention settings</li>
                            </ul>
                        </section>

                        <section class="mb-5">
                            <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="fas fa-user-shield me-2"></i>8. Your Rights (GDPR)</h2>
                            <p>Under GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation) you have the following rights:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><strong>Right of access</strong> - You can request which data we have about you</li>
                                <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> - You can have incorrect data corrected</li>
                                <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> - You can request deletion of your data</li>
                                <li><strong>Right to restriction</strong> - You can restrict the processing of your data</li>
                                <li><strong>Right to data portability</strong> - You can request your data in a common format</li>
                                <li><strong>Right to object</strong> - You can object to certain processing</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>
                                To exercise these rights, contact us via the contact information at the bottom of this page.
                            </p>
                        </section>

                        <section class="mb-5">
                            <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="fas fa-child me-2"></i>9. Children and Privacy</h2>
                            <p>
                                Our services are intended for users who meet Discord's age requirements (minimum 13 years, or 16 years in the EU).
                                We do not knowingly collect data from children younger than this age. If you discover that a child under this age
                                has shared data with us, please contact us.
                            </p>
                        </section>

                        <section class="mb-5">
                            <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="fas fa-edit me-2"></i>10. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
                            <p>
                                We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Significant changes will be communicated
                                via a notification on the dashboard. We recommend reviewing this policy regularly to stay informed
                                about how we protect your data.
                            </p>
                        </section>

                        <section class="mb-5">
                            <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="fas fa-envelope me-2"></i>11. Contact</h2>
                            <p>
                                If you have questions about this privacy policy, want to view, modify, or delete your data, or exercise
                                your GDPR rights, please contact us:
                            </p>
                            <div class="alert alert-info">
                                <p class="mb-2"><i class="fas fa-at me-2"></i><strong>E-mail:</strong> Add your contact email here</p>
                                <p class="mb-2"><i class="fab fa-discord me-2"></i><strong>Discord:</strong> Via the support server</p>
                                <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-link me-2"></i><strong>Website:</strong> <%= typeof process !== 'undefined' && process.env.WEBSITE_URL ? process.env.WEBSITE_URL : 'This website' %></p>
                            </div>
                        </section>

                        <section>
                            <h2 class="h4 mb-3"><i class="fas fa-file-contract me-2"></i>12. Legal Information</h2>
                            <p>
                                This privacy policy is prepared in accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
                                and other applicable privacy legislation.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <strong>Data Controller:</strong> The owner/operator of this bot (see contact information above)
                            </p>
                        </section>

                        <div class="text-center mt-5 pt-4 border-top border-secondary">
                            <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">
                                <i class="fas fa-home me-2"></i>
                                Back to Home
                            </a>
                            <a href="/terms" class="btn btn-outline-light ms-2">
                                <i class="fas fa-file-contract me-2"></i>
                                Gebruiksvoorwaarden
                            </a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
